  "texts": [
    "The issue is that we only have information about t (θ) where the images are.",
    "At these points, we know that ∇t (θ) = 0 and the values of ∇∇t (θ).",
    "We may also know the value of t (θ) (up to a constant), if time delays are measured.",
    "Roughly speaking, time delays measure the potential difference between the image locations, the image locations themselves are probes of the gradient of the potential, while fluxes inform about the tidal field, but these pieces of information are available only at image locations.",
    "Elsewhere the information from lensing must be supplemented with other data where available, and somehow interpolated where necessary."
  ],
